, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Hunaydah ibn Khalid reported: Some of the wives of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said that he would fast the first nine days of the month of Dhul-Hijjah, the day of Ashura, and three days of every month, which would be the first Monday and Thursday of\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33078,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/03\/barakah-dhul-hijjah-arafat\/","url_meta":{"origin":34110,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on \u2018Arafah: Blessings of Dhul-Hijjah, day of Arafat","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 3, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNo days are better to Allah than the first ten days of Dhul-Hijjah.\u201d A man said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, are they better or time spent waging jihad in the way of Allah?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cThey\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":26765,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/08\/19\/offering-not-cut-hair-nails\/","url_meta":{"origin":34110,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Hajj: Those offering sacrifices not cut hair or nails","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 19, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Umm Salamah reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cIf the ten days of Dhul Hijjah begin and one of you intends to sacrifice, let him not remove anything from his hair or skin.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 1977 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Muslim Al-Nawawi said, \u201cThe\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":26841,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2018\/10\/29\/ruqyah-jibreel-dua-prophet\/","url_meta":{"origin":34110,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Ruqyah: Gabriel supplicates over the Prophet for healing","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 29, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Aisha reported: If the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, was afflicted by something, the Angel Gabriel would supplicate over him, saying, \u201cIn the name of Allah, may he cure you, may he heal you from every ailment, from the evil of the envier when he envies,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":58,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2010\/10\/05\/hypocrites-two-faces\/","url_meta":{"origin":34110,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Hypocrisy: Worst people are hypocrites with two faces","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 5, 2010","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The\u00a0Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, among the worst of people is one with two faces, coming with one face to these and another to those.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 7179, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 2526 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi\u00a0(authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":35178,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/02\/09\/honoring-leaders\/","url_meta":{"origin":34110,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Leaders: Honoring elders, scholars, righteous rulers","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 9, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Musa al-Ash\u2019ari reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, part of glorifying Allah is to honor the gray-haired Muslim and the bearer of the Quran, who is neither extravagant nor neglectful of it, and to honor the just ruler.\u201d Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/34110","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=34110"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dail